All Implemented Interfaces:
Proxy
public class BoxGeometryProxy
extends GeometryProxy

A geometry object representing a rectangle.

This geometry object is used for objects that are represented graphically as a rectangle, i.e, group nodes (GroupNodeProxy).

Technically, this class simply is a wrapper of the Rectangle2D class that makes it a subclass of GeometryProxy. The rectangles in a BoxGeometryProxy object are stored and returned as references, so they can be updated directly from outside.

Author:
Robi Malik
